  "body": "Hi,\r\nI ran into several security vulnerabilities related to outdated dependencies.\r\n```\r\nflat  <5.0.1\r\nSeverity: critical\r\n...\r\nminimatch  <3.0.5\r\nSeverity: high\r\n...\r\nrequest  *\r\nSeverity: moderate\r\n...\r\nsemver  <7.5.2\r\nSeverity: moderate\r\n...\r\nword-wrap  *\r\nSeverity: moderate\r\n...\r\n22 vulnerabilities (15 moderate, 4 high, 3 critical)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe most of them stem from eth-gas-reporter@0.2.25 and hardhat@2.16.1 using outdated mocha and glob packages:\r\n```\r\n$ npm list minimatch request semver  word-wrap flat\r\n---@ /home/----/dev/----\r\n├─┬ @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@3.0.0\r\n│ ├─┬ @nomicfoundation/hardhat-verify@1.0.3\r\n│ │ └── semver@6.3.0\r\n│ ├─┬ hardhat-gas-reporter@1.0.9\r\n│ │ └─┬ eth-gas-reporter@0.2.25\r\n│ │   ├─┬ request-promise-native@1.0.9\r\n│ │   │ ├─┬ request-promise-core@1.1.4\r\n│ │   │ │ └── request@2.88.2 deduped\r\n│ │   │ └── request@2.88.2 deduped\r\n│ │   └── request@2.88.2\r\n│ ├─┬ hardhat@2.16.1\r\n│ │ ├─┬ glob@7.2.0\r\n│ │ │ └── minimatch@3.1.2 deduped\r\n│ │ ├─┬ mocha@10.2.0\r\n│ │ │ ├── minimatch@5.0.1\r\n│ │ │ └─┬ yargs-unparser@2.0.0\r\n│ │ │   └── flat@5.0.2\r\n│ │ ├── semver@6.3.0 deduped\r\n│ │ └─┬ solc@0.7.3\r\n│ │   └── semver@5.7.1\r\n│ └─┬ typechain@8.2.0\r\n│   └─┬ glob@7.1.7\r\n│     └── minimatch@3.1.2 deduped\r\n└─┬ solidity-coverage@0.8.3\r\n  ├─┬ mocha@7.1.2\r\n  │ ├─┬ glob@7.1.3\r\n  │ │ └── minimatch@3.0.4 deduped\r\n  │ ├── minimatch@3.0.4\r\n  │ ├─┬ node-environment-flags@1.0.6\r\n  │ │ └── semver@5.7.1\r\n  │ └─┬ yargs-unparser@1.6.0\r\n  │   └── flat@4.1.1\r\n  ├─┬ recursive-readdir@2.2.3\r\n  │ └── minimatch@3.1.2\r\n  ├─┬ sc-istanbul@0.4.6\r\n  │ ├─┬ escodegen@1.8.1\r\n  │ │ └─┬ optionator@0.8.3\r\n  │ │   └── word-wrap@1.2.3\r\n  │ └─┬ glob@5.0.15\r\n  │   └── minimatch@3.1.2 deduped\r\n  └── semver@7.5.3\r\n```\r\nIs there any way to force newer version on your end?\r\n",
